body:
This code compiles without errors with the last Nightly:

```rust
#![feature(const_num_from_num, const_trait_impl)]
#![allow(incomplete_features, dead_code)]
fn main() {
    const X: u64 = u64::from(10_u32);
}
```

While the following two versions:

```rust
#![feature(const_num_from_num)]
#![allow(incomplete_features, dead_code)]
fn main() {
    const X: u64 = u64::from(10_u32);
}
```

```rust
#![allow(incomplete_features, dead_code)]
fn main() {
    const X: u64 = u64::from(10_u32);
}
```

They don't compile and rustc doesn't give a help message like this that helps how to fix the code:

```
  = help: add `#![feature(const_trait_impl)]` to the crate attributes to enable
```
Using:
```
rustc 1.58.0-nightly (e269e6bf4 2021-10-26)
binary: rustc
commit-hash: e269e6bf47f40c9046cd44ab787881d700099252
commit-date: 2021-10-26
host: x86_64-pc-windows-gnu
release: 1.58.0-nightly
LLVM version: 13.0.0
```
